INTRODUCTION
The influence of pragmatism on institutionalism and the role of
rules and habits in decision-making1, whether by
Thorstein Veblen (1990; 1970; 1946) or John Commons (1934; 
1950), has been debated for about twenty years (Bush1993;
Kilpinen1998; Milberg2001; Mirowski2005; Hodgson2004; 
2006; Gronow 2008).
